br>He studied her in silence for a moment then nodded briskly, &quot;Very well, but.. if this is a trap.. &quot; He left the threat unspoken. And then he was gone, vanished near as quickly as he had appeared.<br>Her meeting with Faeolin started nearly as subtly. Faeolin had tracked Kat down. Had watched warily waiting for the right opportunity to make her presence known. Once she had ascertained that there was no trap she stepped out to face Kat. <br>It had taken much convincing before Faeolin would even agree to take part in Kats plan. If the plan backfired, well the consiquences where such that neither wanted to even consider them. The only saving grace to Kats plan was the fact that both Nospiratus and Vresk had agreed to help in it. <br>Faeolin too had left, needing time to think. She would be in contact when Nospiratus returned from his quest. <br>Kat snapped from thoughts of the earlier days events and glanced at the clock once more. It was late at night, and Kat was again pacing the dark bedroom. Four days had passed since he had left. This odd meloncholy that had fallen over her upon his leaving did not seem want to let up. Now add to that the sleepless nights that she found befalling her. She wished she could pinpoint what was wrong with her. This behavoir was odd.<br>Nospiratus had gone to seek council from the Father. And would not be back for several more days. Till then she would have to be especially careful in her conduct and her actions. She would have to make doubly sure not to step on any toes. She would avoid Tzlar and his brother Zirrix at all cost for now. <br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#8E236B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/unospiratus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nospiratus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>The Mad One</span><br>  Posts: 76<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/1/02 11:32:06 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/fvhbrellfrm3.showAd